  "text": "The proposed decimator satisfies the requirements for data processing of 180 Hz baseband ECG signal with stopband attenuation sufficient enough to attenuate the out-of-band high frequency noise while demodulating the -modulated signal. In addition, the error introduced in the reconstructed data is minimal compared to the input signal. Moreover, the proposed decimator is cost effective for hardware implementation due to the filter structures used that do not require any multipliers. Fig. 6 . 10 seconds of ECG signals, (a) MIT-BIH data, output of (b) the proposed the decimation chain and (c) the decimation chain given in [CITATION_1] . Fig. 7 Power of magnitude error between the MIT-BIH data and the output from the (a) proposed decimator and (b) decimator given in [CITATION_2] .",
